Stacks are of LIFO(last in first out operation).
Stacks are called ADT(abstract data type) becauyse we cant directly access elements of stack.
We need some opertation to perform action.

Operations
push()- inserts element into the stack.
pop()- removes the topmost element from the stack.
top()-returns the opmost element of the stack.
size()-returns the number of elements present in the stack at the particular moment.
isEmpty()-returns true if stack is empty else returns false.
